  "text": "As cardiotoxicity is one of the most severe side-effects of DOX, we also examined the effect of the different formulations on zebrafish heart rate after 72 hpi (Fig. 4) . Zebrafish has demonstrated to be a good model for the study of cardiovascular diseases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Despite there are anatomic differences between the zebrafish heart and mammalian heart, several studies have highlighted similarities in the genes and regulatory networks [CITATION_3] . Particularly, [CITATION_4] showed that DOX induces similar cardiac defects in zebrafish as in mammals [CITATION_5] .",
